   827	    /// or to reassign them as we do in `let assert` statements.
   828	    variable_assignment: VariableAssignment,
   829	
   830	    /// All the pattern variables will be assigned a specific value: being bound
   831	    /// to a constructor field, tuple element and so on. Pattern variables never
   832	    /// end up in the generated code but we replace them with their actual value.
   833	    /// We store those values as `EcoString`s in this map; the key is the pattern
   834	    /// variable's unique id.
   835	    ///
   836	    variable_values: HashMap<usize, EcoString>,
   837	
   838	    /// The same happens for bit array segments. Unlike pattern variables, we
