   267	///
   268	/// ```js
   269	/// if (value instanceOf $NonEmptyList) {
   270	///   // ...
   271	/// } else {
   272	///   return [];
   273	/// }
   274	/// ```
   275	///
   276	/// Once that check succeeds we know that now we can access two new values: the
   277	/// first element of the list and the rest of the list! So we need to keep track
